# Large forms — isolate keystroke re-renders

Multi-section controlled forms must not re-render the entire tree on every keystroke.

## Required pattern

1. Keep one `draft` / `setDraft` in the parent shell (save still reads full draft).
2. Split each `FormSection` into a **`memo()` child** (or cache the section element with `useMemo` + field deps).
3. Pass **`setDraft`** (stable) and **only that section’s field values** — never the whole draft object.
4. Read `event.currentTarget.value` **before** calling `setDraft` (updaters run async; `currentTarget` may be null).
5. For address / searchable `Select`s: `memo` the control, keep **stable `onChange`** (`useCallback` + `setDraft`), and do not pass unrelated fields (e.g. address line) into location selects.

```tsx
// ✅ memo section + setDraft + field slices
export const IdentitySection = memo(function IdentitySection({
  danhHieu,
  setDraft,
  disabled,
}: {
  danhHieu: string
  setDraft: Dispatch<SetStateAction<TempleDraft>>
  disabled: boolean
}) {
  return (
    <TextInput
      value={danhHieu}
      onChange={(event) => {
        const value = event.currentTarget.value
        setDraft((current) => ({ ...current, danhHieu: value }))
      }}
      disabled={disabled}
    />
  )
})

// ❌ one component + one draft → every keystroke rebuilds all sections / Selects
function BigForm() {
  const [draft, setDraft] = useState(empty)
  return (
    <>
      <TextInput value={draft.a} onChange={(e) => setDraft({ ...draft, a: e.currentTarget.value })} />
      <ExpensiveAddressFields value={draft.address} onChange={(v) => setDraft({ ...draft, address: v })} />
      {/* dozens more fields */}
    </>
  )
}
```

## Checklist before merging a large form

- [ ] Typing in section A does not re-render section B (React Profiler).
- [ ] Address city/ward `Select`s do not re-render when only the address line changes.
- [ ] No inline `onChange` passed into memoized heavy children unless stabilized.

See `TempleEditorForm.tsx` + `TempleEditorFormSections.tsx` and `VietnamAddressFields.tsx`.
